quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  92,15,"in which none roasts except the most wicked—"
  92,16,"the onewho disbelieved and turned away."
  92,17,"But the most mindful<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><i class=""s"">(of God) </i>will be kept away from it—"
  92,18,"the one who brings{1}his wealth to purify himself,",footnotes:1:The Quran always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.
  92,19,"and not in return for any favor to anyone,"
  92,20,"except for seeking the countenance of his Lord, the Most High."
  92,21,"And he will certainly be well pleased."
  93,1,"By the morning shine."
  93,2,"By the night as it settles—"
  93,3,"your Lord has not abandoned you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, nor has He despised<i class=""s"">(you) </i>."
  93,4,"And indeed the Last is better for you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>than the First,"
  93,5,"and your Lord will certainly give you so that you will be well pleased."
  93,6,"Did He not find you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>an orphan, so He sheltered<i class=""s"">(you) </i>;"
  93,7,"and found you wandering, so He guided<i class=""s"">(you) </i>;"
  93,8,"and found you in need, so He enriched<i class=""s"">(you) </i>?"
  93,9,"So as for the orphan, do<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not subdue;"
  93,10,"and as for the asker, do not rebuke;"
  93,11,"and as for the blessing of your Lord, do talk about it."
  94,1,"Did We not expand your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>chest,"
  94,2,"and lift from you your burden"
  94,3,"which weighed down your back,"
  94,4,"and raised for you your remembrance{1}?",footnotes:1:The Arabic word zhikrcan be translated as ‘remembrance’, ‘mention’ or ‘reminder’.
  94,5,"So indeed, with hardship comes ease;"
  94,6,"indeed, with hardship comes ease."
  94,7,"So whenever you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are done<i class=""s"">(from work) </i>, stand up{1},",footnotes:1:In adoration.
  94,8,"and to your Lord turn wishfully."
